{
  "texts": [
    "The exfoliation energy of van der Waals bonded two-dimensional materials is calculated by calculating the energy difference between each atom in the bulk phase and the corresponding monolayer.",
    "Spin orbit spillage 61 is computed as the disparity between material wavefunctions with and without the inclusion of spin- orbit coupling effects.",
    "All JARVIS-DFT data and classical force field inspired descriptors (CFID) 62 are generated using the JARVIS-Tools software package.",
    "The CFID baseline model is trained using the LightGBM software package 62.",
    "Matbench is an automated benchmark testing platform specifically designed for the field of materials science, designed to evaluate and compare the most advanced ML algorithms that predict various solid material properties."
  ]
}